1. General Provisions

This Software License Agreement (hereinafter referred to as the "Agreement") sets forth the terms of use of the software for the BIIT39 project (hereinafter referred to as the "Software") between Sole Proprietor Nikita Bratukhin (hereinafter referred to as the "Author") and individuals using this Software (hereinafter referred to as the "Users").

2. License

The Author grants the User a non-exclusive right to use the Software worldwide under the following conditions:
- The Software is provided for personal, non-commercial use, educational purposes in technical schools and educational institutions.
- The use of the Software for commercial purposes without the written permission of the Author is prohibited.
- Distribution, leasing, transfer to third parties, modification, or use of Software components in other projects without the written permission of the Author is prohibited.

3. Copyright

All copyright in the Software belongs to the Author. The User agrees to respect the Author's rights, citing the Author's name and a link to the original project when using the Software in accordance with the terms of this Agreement.

4. Disclaimer of Liability

The Software is provided "as is". The Author is not liable for any direct or indirect damages arising from the use or inability to use the Software.

5. Final Provisions

This Agreement may be amended by the Author without any special notice; the new version of the Agreement becomes effective from the moment it is posted on the internet at the address specified by the Author.

Effective Date: February 21, 2024

